<br>
Eventually we left and when he got back on he was able to FD his way all the way out .. Without a single death .. Some Kinda feat that was.  Dont know how he managed it. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#A0B0E0><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub66.ezboard.com/bthearrowoflightcommons.showUserPublicProfile?gid=aevetare>Aevetare</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>The Arrows own Multiple Personality</span><br>  Posts: 285<br> <font color=#000080>(3/4/03 5:03 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub66.ezboard.com/fthearrowoflightcommonsfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=105.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: LD question</span><hr size=1> I think 15 minutes is about standard time to wait for someone in a group situation when they go LD before you find a replacement.  If you are with guildies you may wait as long as possible, but that is up to the people involved and the situation.  Obviously in a mixed group with some people on the east coast they may need to camp to get up for work or school (or tennis) in the morning, so that might leave people on the west coast doing 'PC spawn' duty.<br>
<br>
  Generally it won't take more than 15 minutes to reboot a PC and get connected again.  If there is a more serious problem, 30 minutes might be a good guildline to wait for power to be restored or a PC to be rebooted twice.  I don't think it's fair to have people waiting around for someone to sign back on when unbeknownst to them that person has closed up EQ shop for the night and already gone to bed due to a power outage.<br>
<br>
Aev. <p>A Founder of Arrow of Light</p><i></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub66.ezboard.com/fthearrowoflightcommonsfrm1.showPrevMessage?topicID=105.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub66.ezboard.com/fthearrowoflightcommonsfrm1.showNextMessage?topicID=105.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a self href=http://pub66.ezboard.com/fthearrowoflightcommonsfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=105.topic&index=2><img src=http://www.eq-arrow-of-light.com/aol/images/boardbuttons/reply.gif border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub66.ezboard.com/fthearrowoflightcommonsfrm1.emailToFriend?topicID=105.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub66.ezboard.com/fthearrowoflightcommonsfrm1.threadControl?topicID=105.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/traditional/deleteThread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands</a><br> <a href=http://pub66.ezboard.com/fthearrowoflightcommonsfrm1.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=105.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/ultimate/subscribe.gif width=20 height=20 border=0 alt="Click to receive email notification of replies"> Click to receive email notification of replies</a> <br>  <a href=http://pub66.ezboard.com/fthearrowoflightcommonsfrm1.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=105.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/ultimate/unsubscribe.gif width=20 height=20 border=0 alt="Click to stop receiving email notification of replies"> Click to stop receiving email notification of replies</a> <br> </td><td align="right" valign="top"></td></tr><tr align="right"><td colspan=2><form action=http://pub66.ezboard.com/BBSForum.j